<item>
            <title>[FLINK-9910] Non-queued scheduling failure sometimes does not return the slot</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-9910</link>
                <project id="12315522" key="FLINK">Flink</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Similar to &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-9908&quot; title=&quot;Inconsistent state of SlotPool after ExecutionGraph cancellation &quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;FLINK-9908&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;FLINK-9908&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, it can happen that in case of a non-queued scheduling failure a slot is not properly returned to the &lt;tt&gt;SlotPool&lt;/tt&gt;. The reason for the failure seems to be the exceptional completion of the &lt;tt&gt;allocationFuture&lt;/tt&gt; in &lt;tt&gt;Execution#scheduleForExecution&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
