                            <comment id="16552138" author="githubbot" created="Sun, 22 Jul 2018 19:53:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;GitHub user tillrohrmann opened a pull request:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/flink/pull/6385&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/flink/pull/6385&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-9910&quot; title=&quot;Non-queued scheduling failure sometimes does not return the slot&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;FLINK-9910&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;FLINK-9910&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;scheduling&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; Execution#scheduleForeExecution does not cancel slot future&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ol&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
	&lt;ol&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;What is the purpose of the change&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ol&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;


&lt;p&gt;    In order to properly give back an allocated slot to the SlotPool, one must not complete&lt;br/&gt;
    the result future of Execution#allocateAndAssignSlotForExecution. This commit changes the&lt;br/&gt;
    behaviour in Execution#scheduleForExecution accordingly.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    This PR is based on #6384.&lt;/p&gt;

